    Add a test route to verify server is running.

âœ… PART 3: User Authentication
ğŸ“¦ Extra Packages

npm install bcryptjs jsonwebtoken

Features

    Register and login users

    Hash passwords using bcryptjs

    Generate JWTs on successful login

Routes

POST /api/auth/register
POST /api/auth/login

âœ… PART 4: Middleware Setup

Create authMiddleware to verify JWT and protect task routes:

const auth = (req, res, next) => {
  // Verify JWT and attach user info to request
};

âœ… PART 5: Task CRUD API
Task Model Fields

    title (String)

    description (String)

    status (pending/in-progress/completed)

    dueDate (Date)

    createdBy (User ID)

Routes

POST    /api/tasks
GET     /api/tasks
GET     /api/tasks/:id
PUT     /api/tasks/:id
DELETE  /api/tasks/:id

    Only the task creator can view or edit their tasks.

âœ… PART 6: Filtering, Sorting & Pagination
Example Query

GET /api/tasks?status=completed&sort=dueDate&limit=5&page=2

Mongoose Example

Task.find({ createdBy: req.user.id, status: req.query.status });

âœ… PART 7: Input Validation
ğŸ“¦ Package

npm install express-validator

Validate inputs for required fields, string types, date formats, etc.
âœ… PART 8: Rate Limiting & Security
ğŸ“¦ Packages

npm install express-rate-limit helmet cors

Usage

app.use(helmet());
app.use(cors());
app.use(rateLimit({ windowMs: 15 * 60 * 1000, max: 100 }));

âœ… PART 9: Error Handling & Response Standardization
